# Controlled f_kappa(n_H) calibration sweep — broadened HPC grid (de-conflates n_H from mCloud, sfe).
# ============================================================================================
# WHY: the original 3 calibration anchors (compact/mid/diffuse) varied mCloud AND sfe AND nCore
# together, so "f_kappa(n_H)" was conflated. This grid sweeps nCore FINELY as the primary axis,
# AND varies mCloud + sfe as secondary axes -- so we can SEE whether the f_kappa needed to fire
# the cooling transition (theta->0.95) is a clean function of n_H alone, or also depends on cloud
# mass / star-formation efficiency. f_kappa is swept FINE (13 values) so the firing point is
# BRACKETED precisely at every density (dense fires ~4, diffuse ~60), not extrapolated.
#
# GRID = 7 nCore x 13 f_kappa x 3 mCloud x 3 sfe = 819 runs (HPC; under the 1000 ceiling).
# nCore capped at 1e5 ON PURPOSE -- 1e6 is pathologically stiff/slow for the implicit solve
# (data/dense_stiffness_diag.csv; NOT f_kappa-driven). rCloud stays < the 200 pc rCloud_max
# ceiling across the whole grid (max is mCloud 1e7 x nCore 1e2 ~ 70-85 pc).
#
# RUN (HPC only -- do NOT run 819 combos in an ephemeral container).
# Inspect anywhere:
#   python run.py docs/dev/transition/pdv-trigger/runs/params/sweep_fkappa_nH.param --dry-run   # lists 819
# On Helix, drive it from your laptop (committed scripts travel by git pull):
#   ./docs/dev/transition/pdv-trigger/runs/sync.sh submit    # git pull + emit to /gpfs + sbatch the array
#   ./docs/dev/transition/pdv-trigger/runs/sync.sh watch     # tail the running array
#   ./docs/dev/transition/pdv-trigger/runs/sync.sh collect   # sweep_report.{txt,json}
#   ./docs/dev/transition/pdv-trigger/runs/sync.sh harvest   # make_fkappa_nH_sweep.py -> CSV + PNG
#   ./docs/dev/transition/pdv-trigger/runs/sync.sh down      # pull the CSV/PNG back to commit
# Why the driver (not a bare `--emit-jobs jobs/` + `sbatch`): outputs MUST land on writable
# /gpfs (the repo's /home is read-only at runtime), and the array sbatch needs the Helix
# account/partition/--export=NONE/conda. runs/run_fkappa.sbatch is pre-patched for that;
# sync.sh emits the bundle from $WS (/gpfs) so path2output below resolves there. See REPRODUCE.md Block C.

# --- swept (Cartesian: 7 x 13 x 3 x 3 = 819) ---
nCore                  [1e2, 3e2, 1e3, 3e3, 1e4, 3e4, 1e5]
cooling_boost_kappa    [1.0, 1.5, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0, 6.0, 8.0, 12.0, 16.0, 24.0, 32.0, 48.0, 64.0]
mCloud                 [1e5, 1e6, 1e7]
sfe                    [0.03, 0.1, 0.3]

# --- fixed ---
dens_profile           densPL
densPL_alpha           0
nISM                   0.1
stop_t                 2.0
log_console            False
log_file               True
# relative on purpose: sync.sh emits from /gpfs ($WS) so this resolves to $WS/outputs/sweep_fkappa_nH (writable).
path2output            outputs/sweep_fkappa_nH
